### LINUX COMMANDS

### Public Key Authentication

# Check if ssh client is installed

which ssh

# Generate or create ssh key-pair

ssh-keygen -b 4096

ls -la ~/.ssh

# Remote access

ssh server1@172.100.65.24

# Copying the public key to your server
ssh-copy-id server1@172.100.65.24



### Scheduling Tasks with Cron

crontab -l

# edit cron jobs
